      • isDateValid

        public boolean isDateValid()
        Gets whether or not the date currently entered is valid and not yet passed.
        Returns:
        true if the text entered represents a valid expiry date that has not yet passed, and false if not.

      • getValidDateFields

        public int[] getValidDateFields()
        Gets the expiry date displayed on this control if it is valid, or null if it is not. The return value is given as a length-2 int array, where the first entry is the two-digit month (from 01-12) and the second entry is the four-digit year (2017, not 17).
        Returns:
        an int array of the form {month, year} if the date is valid, or null if it is not
